1
00:01:31,200 --> 00:01:34,918
=Vanished Name=

2
00:01:35,160 --> 00:01:37,848
=Episode 17=
(I Know What Friendship Means)

3
00:01:40,012 --> 00:01:42,333
Xiaoming, I told your mom everything.

4
00:01:46,493 --> 00:01:47,493
Everything?

5
00:01:49,172 --> 00:01:49,892
Everything.

6
00:01:50,853 --> 00:01:52,773
You even told her
you're not the real Bai Shu?

7
00:01:57,292 --> 00:01:58,732
Why did you have to tell her?

8
00:01:58,773 --> 00:02:00,172
She can't keep a secret.

9
00:02:00,252 --> 00:02:01,133
Shut it.

10
00:02:01,613 --> 00:02:02,452
I can keep a secret.

11
00:02:03,292 --> 00:02:04,732
How can you say that about your mom?

12
00:02:07,732 --> 00:02:09,493
I'm sorry.
I shouldn't have mentioned that

13
00:02:09,933 --> 00:02:11,652
in front of you.

14
00:02:12,412 --> 00:02:13,972
I brought up sad memories for you.

15
00:02:15,532 --> 00:02:16,252
It's okay.

16
00:02:17,453 --> 00:02:18,812
I enjoy watching you two argue.

17
00:02:20,132 --> 00:02:23,013
Are you crazy?
You like watching people fight?

18
00:02:23,372 --> 00:02:25,293
If so, you deal with her.
I can't stand her.

19
00:02:26,092 --> 00:02:26,652
Ms. Ren.

20
00:02:29,812 --> 00:02:31,493
I really want to call you Mom.

21
00:02:36,532 --> 00:02:38,013
Good, I have another good daughter.

22
00:02:38,652 --> 00:02:39,972
I'm pretty lucky.

23
00:02:43,652 --> 00:02:45,293
You're much better than the last one.

24
00:02:46,013 --> 00:02:47,852
I wonder if this one can be returned.

25
00:02:49,173 --> 00:02:51,173
But I can't call anyone else Mom.

26
00:02:53,733 --> 00:02:54,493
I understand.

27
00:03:00,132 --> 00:03:01,852
Look, she even wants to call you Mom.

28
00:03:01,852 --> 00:03:03,032
You can't betray us.

29
00:03:03,493 --> 00:03:05,893
You mustn't tell anyone
about us renting a place outside.

30
00:03:06,173 --> 00:03:07,096
Watch that attitude.

31
00:03:09,333 --> 00:03:10,013
Sweetie,

32
00:03:11,092 --> 00:03:14,173
the market area is chaotic.
You can't live there.

33
00:03:15,132 --> 00:03:16,213
Come home with me.

34
00:03:18,893 --> 00:03:20,013
I'll go with you later

35
00:03:20,252 --> 00:03:23,064
to pack up your things
and bring them to our home.

36
00:03:26,200 --> 00:03:27,933
You're actually doing quite well.

37
00:03:28,088 --> 00:03:30,092
Shut up. I'll settle with you later.

38
00:03:31,493 --> 00:03:34,852
You and Xiaoming are good friends.

39
00:03:36,493 --> 00:03:38,532
I know what friendship means.

40
00:03:46,893 --> 00:03:48,733
Xiaofei, stop spinning the top.

41
00:03:51,372 --> 00:03:52,412
Bai Shu.

42
00:03:53,092 --> 00:03:54,692
Move your bedding out of your room.

43
00:03:54,893 --> 00:03:56,568
From today on, you'll sleep on the sofa.

44
00:03:56,933 --> 00:03:58,776
Xiaoming and Bai Shu
will sleep in your room.

45
00:03:59,013 --> 00:04:01,493
Great! Bai Shu is staying with us!

46
00:04:01,493 --> 00:04:04,453
Little thief, put everything you stole
back where it belongs.

47
00:04:07,293 --> 00:04:09,773
Ms. Ren, are you not
making buns anymore?

48
00:04:09,852 --> 00:04:10,972
Why is all the flour gone?

49
00:04:11,572 --> 00:04:13,572
You know what? Those buns...

50
00:04:13,572 --> 00:04:15,692
I used to live well.

51
00:04:16,293 --> 00:04:17,653
I can't endure tiring work.

52
00:04:17,973 --> 00:04:20,853
Making buns for a few days is enough.
How could I keep doing it?

53
00:04:21,093 --> 00:04:22,012
I couldn't take it.

54
00:04:22,653 --> 00:04:25,132
I can't do that, anyway. I quit.

55
00:04:25,332 --> 00:04:27,320
What about earning money?

56
00:04:27,933 --> 00:04:29,413
- You know what?
- Xiaoming.

57
00:04:30,332 --> 00:04:31,733
Come to the market with me.

58
00:04:32,132 --> 00:04:33,368
I'll cook some dishes tonight.

59
00:04:34,332 --> 00:04:36,452
How much are you buying
that you need me to come?

60
00:04:36,733 --> 00:04:37,933
Come on. Go with me.

61
00:04:39,812 --> 00:04:41,720
Don't worry.
Leave everything here to me.

62
00:04:42,252 --> 00:04:43,293
Alright, you stay.

63
00:04:43,692 --> 00:04:45,692
Leave dirty clothes alone.
I'll wash them later.

64
00:04:46,252 --> 00:04:48,252
If Xiaofei annoys you,
just smack him on the head.

65
00:04:49,093 --> 00:04:50,493
Xiaofei and I get along just fine.

66
00:04:51,933 --> 00:04:52,533
Go ahead.

67
00:04:54,572 --> 00:04:55,480
Let me help you.

68
00:05:04,252 --> 00:05:06,012
Don't tell Bai Shu about the bun thing.

69
00:05:07,252 --> 00:05:10,132
You're not relying on her connections.
Why can't I tell her?

70
00:05:10,293 --> 00:05:12,733
I know where those spoiled buns
came from now.

71
00:05:14,012 --> 00:05:14,808
Where?

72
00:05:15,093 --> 00:05:16,572
We offended someone and got framed.

73
00:05:19,132 --> 00:05:19,812
Who?

74
00:05:20,173 --> 00:05:21,733
Think about who you offended.

75
00:05:24,293 --> 00:05:26,493
She locked Bai Shu up at home,
and you let her out.

76
00:05:26,493 --> 00:05:27,452
So she hates you.

77
00:05:28,812 --> 00:05:31,533
You mean Ge Wenjun framed you?

78
00:05:33,332 --> 00:05:35,692
I swear my buns were definitely good.

79
00:05:36,212 --> 00:05:37,413
Then where was the problem?

80
00:05:38,413 --> 00:05:39,173
Think about it.

81
00:05:39,733 --> 00:05:43,372
Right after you took Bai Shu out,
the spoiled bun thing happened.

82
00:05:43,853 --> 00:05:47,252
I ran into Bai Shu's mom
at that same construction site.

83
00:05:47,252 --> 00:05:48,572
I don't think it's a coincidence.

84
00:05:49,772 --> 00:05:51,160
That's just too much.

85
00:05:51,613 --> 00:05:52,853
Come on. Let's report it.

86
00:05:54,132 --> 00:05:55,772
Report it? Do you have any proof?

87
00:05:58,212 --> 00:05:59,493
We just have to take the loss.

88
00:06:00,812 --> 00:06:02,712
Listen, you must not
tell Bai Shu about this.

89
00:06:02,712 --> 00:06:05,372
If she finds out,
she won't stay with us anymore.

90
00:06:06,973 --> 00:06:09,132
Aren't you afraid
Ge Wenjun will cause more trouble?

91
00:06:09,572 --> 00:06:10,173
Yes, I am.

92
00:06:10,973 --> 00:06:13,093
I'm deep in debt
and have no idea how to pay it back.

93
00:06:13,332 --> 00:06:15,160
If something else happens,
I'll be helpless.

94
00:06:17,053 --> 00:06:19,332
Then why did you take Bai Shu in?

95
00:06:21,653 --> 00:06:23,012
I can't watch her living outside.

96
00:06:23,973 --> 00:06:27,132
It's not safe for you two girls
to live in a market area.

97
00:06:27,812 --> 00:06:31,173
If something bad happened,
her mom would surely kill me.

98
00:06:31,533 --> 00:06:33,493
Now she's living comfortably
at our place.

99
00:06:34,093 --> 00:06:35,252
Even if things get too tough,

100
00:06:35,613 --> 00:06:38,252
her mom won't harshly blame us
when she comes to get Bai Shu.

101
00:06:41,132 --> 00:06:44,088
I thought you were kind-hearted.
Turns out you have ulterior motives.

102
00:06:45,093 --> 00:06:45,892
Are you kidding?

103
00:06:47,012 --> 00:06:48,952
Today, I spent nearly 2,000 on you kids.

104
00:06:48,952 --> 00:06:50,733
That was set aside to pay the fine.

105
00:06:51,613 --> 00:06:52,772
Now, it's all gone.

106
00:06:54,933 --> 00:06:56,413
Look, I have only 100 in my pocket.

107
00:06:57,452 --> 00:07:00,293
If we don't figure something out,
our whole family won't survive.

108
00:07:07,572 --> 00:07:10,012
By the way, I haven't asked you yet.

109
00:07:10,012 --> 00:07:11,672
What's your relationship
with He Yuqiong?

110
00:07:12,812 --> 00:07:15,288
What are you talking about?
You got the wrong idea.

111
00:07:16,212 --> 00:07:17,812
Is there something between you two?

112
00:07:18,572 --> 00:07:20,572
The place you rented and the mattress...

113
00:07:22,572 --> 00:07:24,332
You're so annoying!

114
00:07:24,332 --> 00:07:25,560
Listen up, Ren Xiaoming.

115
00:07:25,692 --> 00:07:28,372
Look, if you start puppy love early,
I'll teach you a dear lesson.

116
00:08:01,093 --> 00:08:03,613
Big white buns, one for each.

117
00:08:04,772 --> 00:08:07,973
If they don't eat it,
that's their loss. Let's dig in!

118
00:08:08,733 --> 00:08:11,853
Bai Shu, make yourself at home.
Grab whatever you want to eat.

119
00:08:12,056 --> 00:08:13,912
Whatever you snag
into your bowl is yours.

120
00:08:14,093 --> 00:08:14,733
Okay.

121
00:08:14,892 --> 00:08:15,640
Let's start.

122
00:08:16,853 --> 00:08:17,464
Let's start.

123
00:08:17,613 --> 00:08:18,653
Thanks.

124
00:08:19,332 --> 00:08:21,132
What? What are you doing?

125
00:08:21,572 --> 00:08:25,012
Hey, what a good surprise with you here.

126
00:08:27,252 --> 00:08:28,792
She can't finish it.

127
00:08:29,720 --> 00:08:30,892
This is so much.

128
00:08:30,892 --> 00:08:31,832
Have a bun?

129
00:08:31,832 --> 00:08:33,208
You have this one.

130
00:08:34,253 --> 00:08:36,792
Seriously? Nobody puts food in my bowl.

131
00:08:37,933 --> 00:08:38,732
No.

132
00:08:39,092 --> 00:08:40,173
No! Slow down!

133
00:08:40,173 --> 00:08:42,133
Such a waste! It dropped on the table.

134
00:08:42,332 --> 00:08:43,896
Ms. Ren, have some more.

135
00:08:44,852 --> 00:08:46,253
Thank you for cooking, Ms. Ren.

136
00:08:46,253 --> 00:08:47,212
Mom, eat more.

137
00:08:47,492 --> 00:08:48,413
Eat more.

138
00:08:48,972 --> 00:08:50,612
This is enough.

139
00:08:50,732 --> 00:08:51,653
That's enough.

140
00:08:52,212 --> 00:08:53,092
Ren Xiaoming.

141
00:09:22,893 --> 00:09:24,812
Mr. Liu, it's me, Ge Wenjun.

142
00:09:25,013 --> 00:09:25,773
Hello, Ms. Ge.

143
00:09:26,253 --> 00:09:30,413
Rest assured,
I didn't let workers eat spoiled buns.

144
00:09:30,572 --> 00:09:33,053
I drove that woman away.

145
00:09:33,332 --> 00:09:35,293
She won't be coming back to the site.

146
00:09:35,373 --> 00:09:36,812
Have you demanded compensation?

147
00:09:37,133 --> 00:09:38,612
Compensation?

148
00:09:40,053 --> 00:09:41,173
I understand what you mean.

149
00:09:41,612 --> 00:09:43,133
She must pay compensation.

150
00:09:43,373 --> 00:09:44,893
I'll handle this matter.

151
00:09:45,092 --> 00:09:47,173
Good, we'll do it that way.

152
00:09:53,332 --> 00:09:57,692
Feels so good.
Sleeping in a bed feels so good.

153
00:10:00,933 --> 00:10:04,053
It's all thanks to you, Bai Shu.
Otherwise, I won't be sleeping in a bed.

154
00:10:06,653 --> 00:10:08,253
Sleeping here feels really nice.

155
00:10:09,452 --> 00:10:10,653
This is a real home.

156
00:10:15,933 --> 00:10:17,293
So I'm your family now?

157
00:10:19,653 --> 00:10:20,653
You wish.

158
00:10:21,572 --> 00:10:22,572
Of course you are.

159
00:10:25,133 --> 00:10:26,852
The moment to test the family
has arrived.

160
00:10:26,852 --> 00:10:27,413
What?

161
00:10:30,136 --> 00:10:31,253
Are you crazy?

162
00:10:34,373 --> 00:10:35,413
What's wrong with you?

163
00:10:35,732 --> 00:10:37,013
I farted.

164
00:10:37,133 --> 00:10:40,056
You're crazy, Ren Xiaoming.

165
00:10:41,492 --> 00:10:43,812
Anyway, I did as I wished.

166
00:10:43,852 --> 00:10:45,720
Air this smell out. Come on.

167
00:10:47,293 --> 00:10:49,816
Is this a biological attack?
Good for you.

168
00:10:49,816 --> 00:10:50,773
It smells good.

169
00:10:50,852 --> 00:10:51,653
What?

170
00:10:51,732 --> 00:10:53,812
Why is the smell not gone?
I'm out of here.

171
00:10:53,944 --> 00:10:54,692
No way.

172
00:10:55,773 --> 00:10:58,373
We should endure the smell together.

173
00:11:15,773 --> 00:11:16,452
Bai Shu.

174
00:11:24,013 --> 00:11:25,048
Bai Shu.

175
00:11:26,852 --> 00:11:28,184
Bai Shu.

176
00:11:30,040 --> 00:11:31,160
Bai Shu.

177
00:11:41,133 --> 00:11:43,293
Xiaoming, take this diary with you.

178
00:11:44,692 --> 00:11:46,013
Go as far away as possible.

179
00:11:46,812 --> 00:11:47,812
Don't come back.

180
00:11:48,692 --> 00:11:49,852
Don't contact me anymore.

181
00:12:03,533 --> 00:12:04,173
Hello, Liang Yi.

182
00:12:04,533 --> 00:12:06,332
The second hearing starts tomorrow.

183
00:12:06,692 --> 00:12:09,253
Have you arrived in Qingzhou?
Don't cancel on me again.

184
00:12:10,053 --> 00:12:10,773
Don't worry.

185
00:12:11,612 --> 00:12:12,612
I'm going to the airport.

186
00:12:13,253 --> 00:12:13,852
See you then.

187
00:12:14,373 --> 00:12:15,212
Don't be late.

188
00:12:39,972 --> 00:12:40,632
Mom.

189
00:12:41,293 --> 00:12:43,256
I have a hearing tomorrow.
I'm going to Qingzhou.

190
00:12:43,653 --> 00:12:44,732
Why another hearing?

191
00:12:44,972 --> 00:12:46,452
Why do you fight over the copyright?

192
00:12:46,452 --> 00:12:47,692
Can't you give it up?

193
00:12:47,773 --> 00:12:49,492
Also, I'm divorcing him.

194
00:12:50,413 --> 00:12:51,692
Who filed for divorce first?

195
00:12:52,773 --> 00:12:55,064
I'm asking you,
who initiated the divorce?

196
00:12:55,933 --> 00:12:56,893
Tell me.

197
00:12:56,893 --> 00:12:58,812
That doesn't matter.
I'm divorcing him, anyway.

198
00:13:12,612 --> 00:13:14,852
Why does it have to turn out this way?

199
00:13:16,173 --> 00:13:16,933
(In 2006, Qidaohezi)
Be careful.

200
00:13:18,253 --> 00:13:20,760
Sir, this is practically brand new,

201
00:13:21,092 --> 00:13:22,936
not even used for a full month.

202
00:13:23,253 --> 00:13:24,533
That's not how you explain it.

203
00:13:24,692 --> 00:13:27,533
Since you bought it, it's second-hand,
even if you haven't used it.

204
00:13:27,972 --> 00:13:28,732
Please.

205
00:13:30,332 --> 00:13:30,852
Alright.

206
00:13:31,452 --> 00:13:33,332
The stove plus the steamer, 200 total.

207
00:13:33,572 --> 00:13:34,173
Just 200?

208
00:13:34,773 --> 00:13:36,612
I paid almost 1,000 for this stove.

209
00:13:36,852 --> 00:13:37,732
You're not happy?

210
00:13:38,293 --> 00:13:39,960
Don't sell then. Just keep them.

211
00:13:40,133 --> 00:13:41,053
I'll move them back up.

212
00:13:41,053 --> 00:13:42,572
Aren't you tired of moving them?

213
00:13:42,773 --> 00:13:43,773
Fine, give me the money.

214
00:13:43,933 --> 00:13:44,572
Okay, deal.

215
00:13:45,293 --> 00:13:46,808
I'm telling you, it's a good offer.

216
00:13:47,092 --> 00:13:47,933
More money, please.

217
00:13:50,332 --> 00:13:51,253
Alright, take it.

218
00:13:52,572 --> 00:13:53,912
Find me again if you sell stuff.

219
00:13:56,248 --> 00:13:56,893
Let's go.

220
00:13:56,893 --> 00:13:57,528
Be careful.

221
00:14:02,173 --> 00:14:05,492
Mom, see if we got what we need.
Anything else?

222
00:14:06,492 --> 00:14:08,653
Ms. Ren, why did they take the stove?

223
00:14:09,653 --> 00:14:12,253
I won't need it to make buns.
It blocks the corridor.

224
00:14:12,653 --> 00:14:14,612
But you can't get a good price
at this time.

225
00:14:15,013 --> 00:14:17,812
That's not your concern.
It's cold. Let's go back home.

226
00:14:19,053 --> 00:14:19,933
Let's go, Xiaofei.

227
00:14:30,053 --> 00:14:33,053
Great, we need to pay so much in fines.

228
00:14:33,812 --> 00:14:36,173
Didn't they explain it clearly just now?

229
00:14:36,492 --> 00:14:38,533
Food poisoning,
plus you operated without a license.

230
00:14:38,773 --> 00:14:41,133
You should be thankful
that they just fined you.

231
00:14:41,253 --> 00:14:44,253
Thank heavens then.

232
00:14:45,972 --> 00:14:47,608
What will happen
if I don't pay the fine?

233
00:14:48,092 --> 00:14:49,976
If you don't pay the fine on time,

234
00:14:50,373 --> 00:14:53,053
the court will
forcibly seize all your assets.

235
00:14:53,253 --> 00:14:55,773
The court will
forcibly seize all my assets?

236
00:14:56,332 --> 00:14:57,413
Is the house an asset?

237
00:14:57,612 --> 00:14:58,692
Of course, it is!

238
00:14:58,773 --> 00:14:59,893
Of course, definitely.

239
00:15:00,332 --> 00:15:01,413
Chinese New Year is near.

240
00:15:02,173 --> 00:15:03,572
If the house gets seized too,

241
00:15:03,893 --> 00:15:06,852
we'll all be sleeping on the street.

242
00:15:10,452 --> 00:15:12,732
How am I supposed
to get that much money?

243
00:15:12,933 --> 00:15:14,572
Shouting won't help.

244
00:15:17,773 --> 00:15:18,692
How about...?

245
00:15:21,692 --> 00:15:22,533
How about what?

246
00:15:23,852 --> 00:15:24,653
I have an idea.

247
00:15:24,732 --> 00:15:25,893
What idea? Spit it out!

248
00:15:26,133 --> 00:15:27,013
Let's sell Xiaofei.

249
00:15:27,373 --> 00:15:28,173
In Southeast Asia...

250
00:15:29,692 --> 00:15:31,812
What are you doing?
Why are you hitting me?

251
00:15:35,373 --> 00:15:36,293
Stop!

252
00:15:41,413 --> 00:15:45,653
Why are you provoking me?
I'm already at my wit's end!

253
00:15:51,852 --> 00:15:54,092
Stop crying! Stop it!

254
00:15:56,293 --> 00:15:57,332
Stop crying, sweetie.

255
00:15:57,612 --> 00:15:58,456
Stop crying.

256
00:15:59,253 --> 00:16:00,332
Stop crying, sweetie.

257
00:16:03,092 --> 00:16:03,893
If only I'd known,

258
00:16:04,572 --> 00:16:08,568
I shouldn't have used the house money
to pay the debt for Sun Jinfu.

259
00:16:10,173 --> 00:16:11,492
There, there, stop crying.

260
00:16:11,893 --> 00:16:12,760
Stop crying.

261
00:16:15,013 --> 00:16:16,612
Stop any generous acts.

262
00:16:21,253 --> 00:16:23,092
- Get lost.
- Get lost.

263
00:16:30,933 --> 00:16:31,692
What are you doing?

264
00:16:32,893 --> 00:16:33,413
I can't live.

265
00:16:34,653 --> 00:16:36,572
I'll hang myself there.

266
00:16:39,413 --> 00:16:40,376
Are you serious?

267
00:16:40,492 --> 00:16:43,173
You dare hang yourself?
You're scared to die.

268
00:16:44,253 --> 00:16:45,133
I don't dare die.

269
00:16:47,253 --> 00:16:48,293
I can beg on the streets.

270
00:16:50,452 --> 00:16:52,773
You can't be a beggar
with that thin skin.

271
00:16:52,792 --> 00:16:53,400
You...

272
00:16:53,612 --> 00:16:54,680
- Don't follow me!
- Where are you going?

273
00:16:54,773 --> 00:16:55,972
Go home and cook for Xiaofei.

274
00:16:57,053 --> 00:16:58,812
Are you really going to beg?

275
00:17:02,612 --> 00:17:03,293
Whatever.

276
00:17:06,173 --> 00:17:07,052
Thanks.

277
00:17:07,252 --> 00:17:08,452
Thank you! Come again!

278
00:17:09,853 --> 00:17:12,173
Come take a look! Clearance sale.

279
00:17:12,173 --> 00:17:13,813
Special price.

280
00:17:17,173 --> 00:17:19,452
Excuse me, is this He Yuqiong's stall?

281
00:17:22,133 --> 00:17:24,252
I'm his mom. And you?

282
00:17:24,452 --> 00:17:25,532
I'm Ren Xiaoming's mom.

283
00:17:27,252 --> 00:17:28,600
You're Xiaoming's mom?

284
00:17:29,012 --> 00:17:30,052
Nice to meet you.

285
00:17:30,492 --> 00:17:31,573
Xiaoming comes often.

286
00:17:32,252 --> 00:17:32,813
Take a seat.

287
00:17:34,052 --> 00:17:34,648
Come on.

288
00:17:35,413 --> 00:17:35,928
Sit.

289
00:17:37,613 --> 00:17:40,120
You never came to the parent meetings.
Or we'd have met sooner.

290
00:17:40,373 --> 00:17:41,093
That's right.

291
00:17:41,413 --> 00:17:44,504
Xiaoming is such a good girl.
I really like her.

292
00:17:44,504 --> 00:17:46,200
If she becomes my daughter-in-law,

293
00:17:46,452 --> 00:17:47,893
I'd be over the moon.

294
00:17:49,292 --> 00:17:50,772
I'm here to ask you for money.

295
00:17:51,133 --> 00:17:51,933
What?

296
00:17:53,772 --> 00:17:54,853
He Yuqiong made a bet.

297
00:17:55,252 --> 00:17:57,292
He ate three kilos of cake
and went into shock.

298
00:17:57,532 --> 00:18:00,133
I happened to be there
and took him to the hospital.

299
00:18:00,532 --> 00:18:02,532
His treatment cost nearly 2,000 yuan.

300
00:18:02,532 --> 00:18:04,184
Here's the receipt. Please pay me back.

301
00:18:04,413 --> 00:18:06,520
I told Ren Xiaoming
I'd pay this money back.

302
00:18:06,653 --> 00:18:07,853
Why come to my mom?

303
00:18:08,133 --> 00:18:10,373
He's fine now. I paid for his treatment.

304
00:18:10,853 --> 00:18:13,052
How will you pay it back?
You'll spend your mom's money.

305
00:18:13,252 --> 00:18:15,292
So I ask her for money.
Watch your attitude.

306
00:18:15,853 --> 00:18:18,452
Listen, stop pestering my daughter.

307
00:18:18,893 --> 00:18:21,813
She's at Yucai High School
and aiming for a prestigious university.

308
00:18:23,972 --> 00:18:25,133
Your daughter is outstanding.

309
00:18:25,813 --> 00:18:27,012
My son is good too.

310
00:18:27,893 --> 00:18:28,972
How much do I owe you?

311
00:18:31,732 --> 00:18:34,292
1,987.96 yuan.

312
00:18:39,813 --> 00:18:40,413
Mom.

313
00:18:41,732 --> 00:18:43,613
Here's 475. Take it for now.

314
00:18:44,052 --> 00:18:46,052
I'll pay you back the rest
by the end of the month.

315
00:18:46,292 --> 00:18:47,333
It's a small amount.

316
00:18:47,933 --> 00:18:48,972
You gave her all you have?

317
00:18:49,492 --> 00:18:51,252
How are we going
to pay the delivery guy?

318
00:18:51,732 --> 00:18:52,732
Shut up.

319
00:18:58,573 --> 00:19:00,972
You keep this money
and pay me back by the end of the month.

320
00:19:01,133 --> 00:19:01,813
The receipt.

321
00:19:17,692 --> 00:19:18,573
You...

322
00:19:19,333 --> 00:19:21,173
Why didn't you tell me about it?

323
00:19:22,333 --> 00:19:24,933
I didn't want to make you worry.

324
00:19:25,252 --> 00:19:28,292
Your dad owes money outside,
and the creditors came to our home.

325
00:19:28,573 --> 00:19:31,093
Now you're in debt too?

326
00:19:31,532 --> 00:19:32,972
She came to our stall.

327
00:19:34,052 --> 00:19:35,052
Mom, don't cry.

328
00:19:35,413 --> 00:19:37,853
Are you driving me to death?

329
00:19:39,813 --> 00:19:42,008
Mom, stop crying.

330
00:19:42,232 --> 00:19:44,664
I'll definitely find a way
to pay back the money. It's okay.

331
00:19:45,772 --> 00:19:47,173
Calm down.

332
00:19:51,573 --> 00:19:54,936
(All mothers have their struggles.)

333
00:19:56,012 --> 00:19:57,496
(If it weren't for the kids,)

334
00:19:58,584 --> 00:20:00,333
(I wouldn't be able to do this.)

335
00:20:00,333 --> 00:20:05,208
(Qidaohezi People's Hospital, 2023)

336
00:20:32,692 --> 00:20:33,492
Yuxiu.

337
00:20:41,012 --> 00:20:41,972
Yuxiu.

338
00:21:00,452 --> 00:21:02,452
Grandma, you're so beautiful.

339
00:21:02,532 --> 00:21:03,933
I love you.

340
00:21:07,732 --> 00:21:09,252
Sweetie, come here.

341
00:21:09,653 --> 00:21:10,732
Come closer.

342
00:21:11,732 --> 00:21:12,696
Put your legs up.

343
00:21:13,012 --> 00:21:13,976
On my legs.

344
00:21:18,653 --> 00:21:19,832
Take a nap.

345
00:21:21,772 --> 00:21:22,972
Take a nap.

346
00:21:26,212 --> 00:21:27,492
Take a nap.

347
00:21:27,492 --> 00:21:29,212
(Leaves)
Linden trees shed leaves in October.

348
00:21:30,133 --> 00:21:32,772
How could they appear
inside a statue made in August?

349
00:21:35,333 --> 00:21:36,292
It doesn't make sense.

350
00:21:52,920 --> 00:21:55,864
(Qidaohezi cold wave in 2010)

351
00:22:03,692 --> 00:22:05,492
Cold wave.

352
00:22:06,532 --> 00:22:07,413
There was a cold wave.

353
00:22:12,732 --> 00:22:16,408
(The golden period for solving a case
is 72 hours after it occurs.)

354
00:22:17,052 --> 00:22:21,772
(All clues, like physical evidence,
fingerprints, DNA, and witnesses,)

355
00:22:22,052 --> 00:22:24,173
(will gradually fade with time.)

356
00:22:25,452 --> 00:22:29,093
(Old cases lacking solid clues
are like a veil of fog.)

357
00:22:30,333 --> 00:22:33,573
(What we must do
is leave no stone unturned,)

358
00:22:34,173 --> 00:22:36,728
(uncover the truth,
and pierce through the fog.)

359
00:22:37,373 --> 00:22:38,133
What are you doing?

360
00:22:38,252 --> 00:22:39,292
You scared me!

361
00:22:44,413 --> 00:22:46,252
Why didn't you come alone
without telling me?

362
00:22:47,853 --> 00:22:50,972
Could a cold wave make the linden trees
shed their leaves early?

363
00:22:51,532 --> 00:22:55,732
There was a cold wave in August 2010.
All the leaves fell.

364
00:22:56,133 --> 00:22:57,292
Haven't you read the novel?

365
00:22:58,012 --> 00:23:00,333
If you had, you wouldn't be asking me.

366
00:23:01,732 --> 00:23:04,972
Why do you keep telling me
to read the novel?

367
00:23:05,173 --> 00:23:07,173
Listen, I want to help you.

368
00:23:07,373 --> 00:23:08,888
Haven't you wanted to solve the case?

369
00:23:12,653 --> 00:23:13,853
Can you be more specific?

370
00:23:15,052 --> 00:23:15,972
No comment.

371
00:23:18,613 --> 00:23:22,052
A friendly reminder, the diary
wasn't originally written this way.

372
00:23:22,893 --> 00:23:25,052
Find the diary,
and you'll find the answers.

373
00:23:41,012 --> 00:23:42,732
There's a cemetery on the outskirts.

374
00:23:43,292 --> 00:23:46,893
The hill behind it is planted
with a foreigner's homesickness.

375
00:23:47,613 --> 00:23:50,613
The homesickness
is called North American linden.

376
00:23:51,800 --> 00:23:53,208
(Leaf, North American linden, cemetery)

377
00:23:53,532 --> 00:23:54,492
Cemetery?

378
00:23:55,613 --> 00:23:56,853
Rest Cemetery.

379
00:23:58,413 --> 00:24:00,760
Captain Li,
how did you know it was Rest Cemetery?

380
00:24:01,492 --> 00:24:03,613
Bai Shu worked at Rest Cemetery.

381
00:24:07,160 --> 00:24:07,512
(Rest Cemetery)

382
00:24:07,512 --> 00:24:09,732
So the novel is indeed connected
to this case.

383
00:24:16,893 --> 00:24:20,664
Captain Li, I've read
the Leopard and Graveyard chapter.

384
00:24:21,173 --> 00:24:22,452
First, the location...

385
00:24:22,452 --> 00:24:23,212
Hold on.

386
00:24:27,292 --> 00:24:33,052
The leopard died on the hill
behind a cemetery with linden leaves.

387
00:24:33,373 --> 00:24:36,452
That matches our guess
about the primary crime scene.

388
00:24:36,653 --> 00:24:40,173
Second, the time:
there was a cold wave in 2010.

389
00:24:40,933 --> 00:24:43,452
That coincides with the renovation
of Qidian Middle School.

390
00:24:43,893 --> 00:24:45,813
Finally, the cause of death.

391
00:24:46,212 --> 00:24:50,212
In the novel, a branch was stuck
in the leopard's neck.

392
00:24:50,692 --> 00:24:53,492
Our autopsy report
shows a broken cervical spine.

393
00:24:54,173 --> 00:24:56,252
Neck, cervical spine.

394
00:24:56,772 --> 00:24:58,488
Isn't that another coincidence?

395
00:24:59,772 --> 00:25:04,173
It's like this novel is about our case.

396
00:25:05,853 --> 00:25:06,813
So what?

397
00:25:07,252 --> 00:25:09,373
You can't use a novel as evidence.

398
00:25:09,933 --> 00:25:13,208
But Bai Shu said
the novel is based on a diary.

399
00:25:13,532 --> 00:25:15,093
A diary can be used as evidence.

400
00:25:16,052 --> 00:25:18,732
But Bai Shu said
the diary is in Ren Xiaoming's hands.

401
00:25:18,933 --> 00:25:20,452
Ren Xiaoming denied having it.

402
00:25:20,853 --> 00:25:21,613
So,

403
00:25:23,212 --> 00:25:27,212
(Diary)
how can we prove it really exists?

404
00:25:27,853 --> 00:25:29,333
When is the copyright hearing?

405
00:25:30,133 --> 00:25:30,853
Tomorrow.

406
00:25:34,732 --> 00:25:38,653
Would Ren Xiaoming
present the diary as evidence in court

407
00:25:39,012 --> 00:25:41,592
to win the copyright hearing?

408
00:25:42,492 --> 00:25:44,173
(The diary is the most direct evidence.)

409
00:25:44,692 --> 00:25:46,040
(She will definitely present it.)

410
00:25:46,732 --> 00:25:47,373
Yanzi.

411
00:25:48,373 --> 00:25:49,528
Contact the Qingzhou court.

412
00:25:50,093 --> 00:25:52,653
Once Ren Xiaoming presents the diary
in the court hearing,

413
00:25:53,173 --> 00:25:54,413
they need to contact us.

414
00:25:54,552 --> 00:25:55,133
Yes.

415
00:25:58,692 --> 00:26:00,600
(This is
Qingzhou Intermediate People's Court.)

416
00:26:01,173 --> 00:26:04,536
(This is the copyright case
of Ren Xiaoming and Liu Xiaoran.)

417
00:26:04,732 --> 00:26:05,848
(Court is now in session.)

418
00:26:08,252 --> 00:26:10,212
As Liu Xiaoran's wife and the defendant,

419
00:26:10,452 --> 00:26:12,052
I can honestly say

420
00:26:12,373 --> 00:26:14,712
(Representative Agent, Plaintiff)
that Liu Xiaoran, since 2021,

421
00:26:15,448 --> 00:26:17,052
has been in a poor creative state.

422
00:26:17,368 --> 00:26:18,292
(Defendant, Authorized Agent)

423
00:26:18,292 --> 00:26:21,112
He completely stopped writing novels.

424
00:26:21,772 --> 00:26:24,012
Also, the story of a TV series
he was involved in

425
00:26:24,452 --> 00:26:27,893
was written by a ghostwriter
hired by his company.

426
00:26:29,933 --> 00:26:34,613
So Liu Xiaoran plagiarized my work
after he lost his creative inspiration.

427
00:26:34,853 --> 00:26:36,133
He admitted it himself.

428
00:26:37,052 --> 00:26:40,212
It can be seen in the video call
between him and my mother.

429
00:26:40,413 --> 00:26:41,093
Thank you.

430
00:26:49,373 --> 00:26:50,853
Plaintiff Ren Xiaoming

431
00:26:51,772 --> 00:26:56,772
is my wife,
who has lived with me for ten years.

432
00:26:58,373 --> 00:27:00,933
To seek financial gain,

433
00:27:02,252 --> 00:27:03,492
she disregarded the facts

434
00:27:05,573 --> 00:27:09,012
and made baseless charges against me.

435
00:27:09,853 --> 00:27:12,333
And before the trial,

436
00:27:13,133 --> 00:27:16,012
she induced me to lie to her mother.

437
00:27:16,933 --> 00:27:19,853
She wanted to save face
in front of her family.

438
00:27:21,212 --> 00:27:25,252
I didn't guard against her
and fell into her trap.

439
00:27:26,292 --> 00:27:28,692
I solemnly declare here

440
00:27:31,212 --> 00:27:35,544
that the original concept
for the novel "Breathe" is mine.

441
00:27:36,573 --> 00:27:40,212
I wrote it myself, word by word.

442
00:27:41,093 --> 00:27:44,613
It has nothing to do with Ren Xiaoming.

443
00:27:54,968 --> 00:27:59,864
(Qingzhou, 2014)

444
00:28:02,732 --> 00:28:05,853
They recruited us back
and made me live here.

445
00:28:07,212 --> 00:28:08,282
This is how they treat us.

446
00:28:08,282 --> 00:28:10,252
This is what I am worth now.

447
00:28:11,933 --> 00:28:12,893
Sorry.

448
00:28:13,653 --> 00:28:16,093
I'm not Mao Dun and we aren't in Guilin.

449
00:28:20,133 --> 00:28:23,292
You are still a junior lecturer now.

450
00:28:23,893 --> 00:28:25,452
It's good to get a dorm like this.

451
00:28:25,972 --> 00:28:27,012
What do you mean?

452
00:28:27,573 --> 00:28:30,972
Are you mocking me?
My rank is low, and I don't deserve it?

453
00:28:33,212 --> 00:28:36,292
I feel they disrespect me
and haven't given me what I deserve.

454
00:28:36,532 --> 00:28:38,452
I'm a writer.

455
00:28:38,972 --> 00:28:41,532
No bookshelf, no chair, nothing.

456
00:28:42,173 --> 00:28:43,448
Just one desk.

457
00:28:43,448 --> 00:28:45,532
The bed is for both of us.

458
00:28:45,972 --> 00:28:47,252
There is something on the wall.

459
00:28:47,492 --> 00:28:48,760
What is this?

460
00:28:49,853 --> 00:28:51,972
I truly can't stand it.

461
00:28:51,972 --> 00:28:53,848
Sooner or later, I will resign.

462
00:28:56,373 --> 00:28:57,853
You know what? I know a guy

463
00:28:58,573 --> 00:28:59,492
named Chen Junhang.

464
00:29:00,373 --> 00:29:01,373
He told me

465
00:29:01,972 --> 00:29:04,252
about a lucrative method nowadays.

466
00:29:05,853 --> 00:29:07,853
It's writing articles on social media.

467
00:29:09,012 --> 00:29:10,933
You first establish your persona.

468
00:29:11,933 --> 00:29:14,373
It doesn't matter
if your articles are a bit subjective.

469
00:29:14,776 --> 00:29:16,216
It's okay as long as people read it.

470
00:29:16,413 --> 00:29:19,052
Just get clicks and traffic,

471
00:29:19,532 --> 00:29:20,440
and you'll get money.

472
00:29:21,252 --> 00:29:21,944
What do you say?

473
00:29:23,333 --> 00:29:25,624
Xiaoran, it's been over a year
since we got married.

474
00:29:25,624 --> 00:29:26,853
You've changed so much.

475
00:29:30,772 --> 00:29:31,452
I...

476
00:29:31,772 --> 00:29:32,853
You've become restless.

477
00:29:33,893 --> 00:29:34,653
Restless?

478
00:29:35,692 --> 00:29:37,853
Why do you suddenly
have so many negative feelings?

479
00:29:41,692 --> 00:29:43,532
I chased you for years
and finally married you.

480
00:29:43,653 --> 00:29:45,052
I have to make you happy.

481
00:29:45,532 --> 00:29:48,093
I'm married. I have a home and you.

482
00:29:48,252 --> 00:29:49,893
I want to make you happy.

483
00:29:50,052 --> 00:29:52,012
I studied hard for so many years.

484
00:29:52,212 --> 00:29:54,456
I definitely didn't come back for this.

485
00:29:55,252 --> 00:29:55,933
Look.

486
00:29:58,052 --> 00:29:58,853
Look over there.

487
00:29:59,093 --> 00:30:01,532
Those people who used to praise me

488
00:30:01,732 --> 00:30:04,173
are now hiding in some corner
and laughing at me.

489
00:30:05,692 --> 00:30:08,972
All this is just temporary.
It will all get better.

490
00:30:25,373 --> 00:30:26,532
I'm sorry, Xiaoming.

491
00:30:28,373 --> 00:30:29,653
I vented a bit.

492
00:30:30,413 --> 00:30:31,133
- I lost my composure.
- It's okay.

493
00:30:31,133 --> 00:30:31,772
It's okay.

494
00:30:32,732 --> 00:30:33,853
You're absolutely right.

495
00:30:35,532 --> 00:30:36,772
It's all temporary.

496
00:30:41,093 --> 00:30:42,212
Come on, Xiaoran.

497
00:30:42,613 --> 00:30:43,452
Come on.

498
00:30:46,012 --> 00:30:48,052
What do you think
our room is missing the most

499
00:30:49,893 --> 00:30:50,732
right now?

500
00:30:51,613 --> 00:30:52,492
What's missing?

501
00:30:53,653 --> 00:30:56,413
Do you even need to ask?
Look, everything is missing!

502
00:30:56,532 --> 00:30:57,653
Think about it.

503
00:30:57,893 --> 00:30:58,616
What's missing?

504
00:30:58,616 --> 00:30:59,853
What do you think is missing?

505
00:30:59,893 --> 00:31:01,452
I don't know.

506
00:31:01,452 --> 00:31:02,613
What do you think is missing?

507
00:31:03,212 --> 00:31:03,893
What's missing?

508
00:31:03,893 --> 00:31:04,573
Curtains.

509
00:31:11,933 --> 00:31:15,012
Could you come back
to my hometown with me?

510
00:31:15,732 --> 00:31:16,373
Why?

511
00:31:19,012 --> 00:31:20,333
It's my mom.

512
00:31:21,012 --> 00:31:23,853
She is unhappy about us getting married.

513
00:31:24,292 --> 00:31:25,528
She thinks I lied to her.

514
00:31:26,732 --> 00:31:30,853
Aren't your parents curious
about me at all?

515
00:31:37,012 --> 00:31:37,853
Hold on.

516
00:31:38,212 --> 00:31:39,093
Actually,

517
00:31:40,692 --> 00:31:41,653
as you know,

518
00:31:42,532 --> 00:31:43,413
my parents

519
00:31:43,972 --> 00:31:47,448
are intellectuals
who aren't very sociable.

520
00:31:48,012 --> 00:31:51,012
They don't care much
about superficial ceremonies.

521
00:31:52,532 --> 00:31:55,492
It's just a formality.
We won't live with them.

522
00:31:56,972 --> 00:31:57,613
Okay.

523
00:31:58,692 --> 00:32:00,333
We'll meet right here in Qingzhou.

524
00:32:01,052 --> 00:32:02,413
I'll have my parents come over.

525
00:32:03,212 --> 00:32:04,344
Your mom will come too.

526
00:32:04,613 --> 00:32:05,656
This place is suitable.

527
00:32:05,853 --> 00:32:07,133
We will have a meal together.

528
00:32:07,933 --> 00:32:08,632
Okay.

529
00:32:11,052 --> 00:32:11,772
Also,

530
00:32:13,133 --> 00:32:15,992
although my family situation is decent,

531
00:32:16,413 --> 00:32:17,613
my parents have taught me

532
00:32:17,853 --> 00:32:21,292
that I need to make it on my own.

533
00:32:21,492 --> 00:32:22,753
- And no material...
- I know.

534
00:32:22,753 --> 00:32:24,692
You've told me a million times already.

535
00:32:25,012 --> 00:32:27,173
The same with my family.
My mom won't help me either.

536
00:32:27,292 --> 00:32:29,532
We'll rely on ourselves. Come on.

537
00:32:38,488 --> 00:32:40,093
(Before the trial)

538
00:32:40,093 --> 00:32:42,532
The video evidence
we submitted just doesn't hold up.

539
00:32:43,452 --> 00:32:46,212
Liu Xiaoran submitted his writing drafts
from his computer.

540
00:32:46,573 --> 00:32:49,933
Without stronger evidence,
we're definitely going to lose.

541
00:32:51,052 --> 00:32:54,452
(The moment the diary comes out,
he loses for sure.)

542
00:32:56,212 --> 00:32:57,613
I know what I want.

543
00:32:59,692 --> 00:33:00,292
What?

544
00:33:01,492 --> 00:33:03,192
Are you even listening to me?

545
00:33:03,452 --> 00:33:05,853
Do you have any evidence or not?

546
00:33:08,413 --> 00:33:08,972
No.

547
00:33:10,573 --> 00:33:11,532
We're going to lose.

548
00:33:16,333 --> 00:33:18,853
The evidence provided
by the plaintiff in this case

549
00:33:19,292 --> 00:33:21,613
is insufficient
to prove the facts claimed.

550
00:33:22,573 --> 00:33:24,292
The judgment is as follows.

551
00:33:24,772 --> 00:33:25,853
- Dismiss
- (Strange.)

552
00:33:25,853 --> 00:33:27,133
the plaintiff's claims.

553
00:33:27,133 --> 00:33:29,452
(Why would she rather lose the lawsuit)

554
00:33:29,772 --> 00:33:31,448
(than present the diary?)

555
00:33:32,772 --> 00:33:34,972
She handed over the diary
we wrote together

556
00:33:35,052 --> 00:33:36,344
to her husband for publication.

557
00:33:36,653 --> 00:33:38,413
What diary?
How come I didn't know about it?

558
00:33:39,333 --> 00:33:41,532
(Could it be
that she really doesn't have it?)

559
00:33:42,212 --> 00:33:44,568
(Why does Bai Shu insist she does?)

560
00:33:45,093 --> 00:33:46,532
(Which one of them is lying?)

561
00:33:47,452 --> 00:33:49,972
I just told you to read the novel.
You must read it.

562
00:33:50,292 --> 00:33:51,704
She doesn't have the final say.

563
00:33:52,413 --> 00:33:53,853
She has to show evidence.

564
00:33:54,413 --> 00:33:57,212
(What's going on
between Ren Xiaoming and Bai Shu?)

565
00:34:14,232 --> 00:34:18,296
(Diary)

566
00:34:21,816 --> 00:34:24,696
(Ren Xiaoming)

567
00:34:27,192 --> 00:34:29,912
(Bai Shu)

568
00:34:30,572 --> 00:34:34,052
(What roles do Ren Xiaoming
and Bai Shu play in this story?)

569
00:34:36,333 --> 00:34:37,452
Ren Xiaoming.

570
00:34:37,972 --> 00:34:40,773
Are you trying to use the trial
to prove the diary doesn't exist?

571
00:34:42,452 --> 00:34:43,452
What are you up to?

572
00:35:52,893 --> 00:35:53,492
Xiaoming.

573
00:36:00,052 --> 00:36:00,652
Xiaoming.

574
00:36:18,213 --> 00:36:21,693
Thank you
for not destroying me in court today.

575
00:36:24,373 --> 00:36:25,144
It's okay.

576
00:36:28,012 --> 00:36:29,773
I'll still get the copyright back.

577
00:36:33,213 --> 00:36:33,773
Okay.

578
00:36:37,933 --> 00:36:38,733
Well then,

579
00:36:40,012 --> 00:36:41,652
thank you for not presenting the diary.

580
00:36:41,853 --> 00:36:42,456
The diary?

581
00:36:43,893 --> 00:36:44,612
What diary?

582
00:36:46,452 --> 00:36:49,773
Didn't you say in court
that you typed your book word by word?

583
00:36:51,652 --> 00:36:52,693
What diary?

584
00:36:56,532 --> 00:36:57,528
Are you okay?

585
00:37:04,452 --> 00:37:05,400
Good.

586
00:37:08,853 --> 00:37:10,172
I'll go get you something to eat.

587
00:37:17,496 --> 00:37:19,733
The copyright lawsuit is over.

588
00:37:20,373 --> 00:37:21,413
Get ready.

589
00:37:22,532 --> 00:37:23,773
For the divorce lawsuit.

590
00:37:31,893 --> 00:37:32,652
Why?

591
00:37:37,652 --> 00:37:39,012
Why do you insist on divorcing me?

592
00:37:41,132 --> 00:37:42,652
We were fine before.

593
00:37:43,652 --> 00:37:46,652
Why divorce me now?

594
00:37:48,853 --> 00:37:50,232
For an apple,

595
00:37:52,693 --> 00:37:54,572
the core goes bad first.

596
00:37:56,452 --> 00:37:58,052
But from the outside,

597
00:37:58,893 --> 00:38:00,693
it looks like a good apple.

598
00:38:01,572 --> 00:38:02,853
Only when you bite into it

599
00:38:05,172 --> 00:38:06,012
do you realize

600
00:38:08,333 --> 00:38:09,413
the apple is rotten.

601
00:38:11,532 --> 00:38:12,373
It's no good anymore.

602
00:38:16,092 --> 00:38:18,680
The day you chose
to publish the new book,

603
00:38:21,773 --> 00:38:24,213
the apple was bitten.

604
00:38:32,012 --> 00:38:33,213
You bit the apple.

605
00:38:36,572 --> 00:38:37,452
Be responsible.

606
00:38:48,012 --> 00:38:48,853
Mr. Liu.

607
00:38:52,213 --> 00:38:54,008
It's a good thing we don't have kids.

608
00:38:57,933 --> 00:38:58,572
You...

609
00:39:01,012 --> 00:39:01,733
Well,

610
00:39:05,293 --> 00:39:07,052
neither of us is a good person.

611
00:39:10,532 --> 00:39:11,972
To be parents, you have to learn

612
00:39:13,693 --> 00:39:15,172
how to be decent people first.

613
00:39:32,213 --> 00:39:32,893
Ma'am.

614
00:39:33,532 --> 00:39:34,092
Ma'am.

615
00:39:34,773 --> 00:39:35,384
Ma'am.

616
00:39:35,612 --> 00:39:36,728
(Breathe)
Why are you sleeping here?

617
00:39:37,452 --> 00:39:38,972
- I brought you breakfast.
- Captain Li.

618
00:39:43,532 --> 00:39:45,240
I'll swap my porridge for your soy milk.

619
00:39:45,773 --> 00:39:47,452
Since you don't eat it,
why did you buy it?

620
00:39:47,773 --> 00:39:49,132
Alright, forget the breakfast.

621
00:39:49,132 --> 00:39:49,853
Put it there.

622
00:39:50,012 --> 00:39:51,672
Sit down.
Let's sort out the case details.

623
00:39:57,293 --> 00:40:00,052
I had a new idea last night.

624
00:40:00,413 --> 00:40:03,532
The Leopard and Graveyard chapter
is actually a murder case.

625
00:40:04,012 --> 00:40:05,432
The one who died is the leopard.

626
00:40:06,172 --> 00:40:11,172
The leopard is used
to conceal the victim's true identity.

627
00:40:13,132 --> 00:40:14,232
Look at this line here.

628
00:40:14,893 --> 00:40:19,052
That leopard appeared again.

629
00:40:20,213 --> 00:40:21,012
What does this mean?

630
00:40:21,452 --> 00:40:24,253
This shows that leopard appeared before.

631
00:40:25,172 --> 00:40:27,253
So, if we think of it as a person,

632
00:40:27,612 --> 00:40:31,384
that person must have appeared
in other chapters of this novel.

633
00:40:32,213 --> 00:40:33,012
So, guys.

634
00:40:33,624 --> 00:40:34,373
Let's start.

635
00:40:34,532 --> 00:40:35,612
Time is tight.

636
00:40:36,853 --> 00:40:37,893
One book per person.

637
00:40:38,572 --> 00:40:40,972
We'll search chapter by chapter

638
00:40:40,972 --> 00:40:42,592
and examine character by character.

639
00:40:42,592 --> 00:40:43,733
We'll definitely find clues.

640
00:40:44,012 --> 00:40:44,893
Read the novel?

641
00:40:44,893 --> 00:40:45,532
Start.

642
00:40:46,253 --> 00:40:48,213
Just do what she says.

643
00:40:48,213 --> 00:40:48,664
(New message)

644
00:40:50,872 --> 00:40:52,248
(Ren Xiaoming)

645
00:41:00,536 --> 00:41:05,592
(Ren Xiaoming)

646
00:41:06,172 --> 00:41:06,853
Hello?

647
00:41:08,172 --> 00:41:08,853
Meng.

648
00:41:09,373 --> 00:41:10,532
Can you do me a favor?

649
00:41:11,213 --> 00:41:12,572
Go ahead. What favor?

650
00:41:13,012 --> 00:41:14,773
I just sent you a string of numbers.

651
00:41:14,853 --> 00:41:16,056
Could you send it to Bai Shu?

652
00:41:17,693 --> 00:41:19,160
Why don't you send it yourself?

653
00:41:19,853 --> 00:41:22,213
She blocked me.
How can I send it to her?

654
00:41:23,893 --> 00:41:25,733
What do these numbers mean?

655
00:41:26,733 --> 00:41:28,253
It's a secret communication code

656
00:41:28,972 --> 00:41:30,333
between her and me.

657
00:41:34,572 --> 00:41:35,352
How to decode it?

658
00:41:36,172 --> 00:41:38,572
It's a secret. How can I tell you?

659
00:41:40,693 --> 00:41:41,733
This isn't illegal, is it?

660
00:41:42,853 --> 00:41:44,052
Will you guys arrest me?

661
00:41:46,413 --> 00:41:48,413
Please do me a favor. I'm begging you.

662
00:41:49,572 --> 00:41:51,012
Okay, I'll help you.

663
00:41:52,172 --> 00:41:54,452
Alright, I'll treat you to a meal later.

664
00:41:54,773 --> 00:41:55,893
Got it. Bye.

665
00:41:58,773 --> 00:41:59,652
What did she send?

666
00:42:00,373 --> 00:42:01,012
Copy it down.

667
00:42:02,733 --> 00:42:03,933
101925,

668
00:42:05,132 --> 00:42:06,572
371512,

669
00:42:07,612 --> 00:42:09,172
661719,

670
00:42:09,853 --> 00:42:11,293
362622,

671
00:42:11,572 --> 00:42:13,413
530722,

672
00:42:13,853 --> 00:42:15,253
300507,

673
00:42:15,373 --> 00:42:16,933
051613.

674
00:42:17,172 --> 00:42:18,172
613.

675
00:42:18,413 --> 00:42:20,012
010621,

676
00:42:20,172 --> 00:42:21,693
051215,

677
00:42:22,012 --> 00:42:23,572
142608,

678
00:42:24,893 --> 00:42:26,360
160915,

679
00:42:27,576 --> 00:42:29,612
- 91...
- 160914,

680
00:42:29,853 --> 00:42:31,853
082528,

681
00:42:32,092 --> 00:42:34,132
060319.

682
00:42:34,733 --> 00:42:35,333
That's all.

683
00:42:40,733 --> 00:42:42,452
Ma'am, the master code?

684
00:42:43,893 --> 00:42:45,893
The one often used in spy dramas.

685
00:42:47,832 --> 00:42:50,052
Old Ghost, you decode them.

686
00:42:51,172 --> 00:42:54,572
Without the master code,
it's useless to have these numbers.

687
00:42:56,933 --> 00:42:58,972
Since she's playing
Cliff Walkers with us,

688
00:42:59,532 --> 00:43:01,333
we'll just Let the Bullets Fly.

689
00:43:05,000 --> 00:43:12,808
=Vanished Name=
